# A public IP pool is simply a set of IPv4 CIDR blocks allocated to a tenancy. 
# These CIDR blocks can be all or part of a BYOIP CIDR block. Public IP CIDR blocks
# assigned to a pool are only available for your tenancy. Public IP pools are 
# available as a source for IP allocation when launching a NAT gateway, load balancer,
# or compute instance. You can add more IP CIDR blocks to a public IP pool at any time.


Prerequisites:

- BYOIP addresses